article.description: Jamel Waters and Torloft Thomas combined to score 29 points and Alabama State beat Prairie View A&M, 73-68 Saturday night, extending its season-long win streak to four games.
article.headline: Alabama State wins 4th straight, tops Prairie View 73-68
article.linkText: Alabama State wins 4th straight, tops Prairie View 73-68
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas -- Jamel Waters and Torloft Thomas combined to score 29 points and Alabama State beat Prairie View A&M, 73-68 Saturday night, extending its season-long win streak to four games. Prairie View came into the game after sweeping Arkansas-Pine Bluff and Mississippi Valley State on the road and was in search of its first three-game winning streak of the season. The teams played to a 35-35 draw at intermission, but Alabama State led by as many as 18 points midway through the second half after Waters hit a jumper to make it 62-44. Waters shot 6 of 13 from the field, including 3 of 6 from beyond the arc, to finish with 15 points to pace Alabama State (12-15, 7-8 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Thomas hit 4 of 8 from the field and was also 3 of 6 from long range. Tevin Bellinger had 16 points and Jayrn Johnson added 15 to lead Prairie View (5-22, 5-10).
